05. Walkthrough the LLD

=> The core of the system is the UrlShortenerService class
=> This service is responsible for two main operations:
    shortening a long URL and redirecting from a short URL
=> To achieve fast O(1) lookups in both directions, I am using two HashMaps
=> shortToLong → Maps a short URL to its corresponding UrlMapping object.
This is mainly used for redirection.
=> longToShort → Maps the original long URL to its UrlMapping object.
   This helps us avoid creating duplicate short URLs for the same long URL.
=> The central entity is the UrlMapping class.
=> UrlMapping class contains longUrl, shortUrl, createdBy, createdAt, expiresAt, clickCount
=> UrlShortenerService has a composition relationship with UrlMapping (1 to many).
   The service manages and owns all the UrlMappings.
=> UrlMapping has an association with User (1 to 0..1).
   A short URL may or may not be created by a registered user.
=> shortenUrl(longUrl, customAlias): Checks if the long URL already exists using the longToShort map.
If not, it generates a new short URL (or uses the custom alias),
creates a UrlMapping, and stores it in both maps.
=> redirect(shortUrl): Looks up the short URL in the shortToLong map,
increments the click count, and returns the original long URL.
=> getStats(shortUrl): Returns the complete UrlMapping object containing all statistics.

